sql:
SELECT p_value
FROM snps
WHERE nobs > 500;

SELECT COUNT(snp_id) AS snp_count
FROM snp_traits
WHERE trait_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Tightly linked genetic variations refer to SNPs with an effect size greater than 1.0; 
- Significant impact refers to a p-value, which is a measure of the strength of evidence against a null hypothesis; 
- Numerous observations refer to nobs > 1000; 
- Substantial evidence refers to groups with more than 10 SNPs.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(snp_id) AS snp_count
FROM snp_diseases
WHERE disease_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(effect_size) AS average_effect_size
FROM study_snps
WHERE study_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(p_value) AS average_p_value
FROM study_snps
WHERE study_id = 1;
